    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-02T03:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-02T03:35:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/12–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-02T12:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 2, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 2—9:20
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1039. Text of Soviet note of November 26 was released to press here yesterday
                    afternoon. Since I assume Iranian Ambassador Washington has it, full text is not
                    being telegraphed. Body of note consists of denials of various assertions made
                    in Iran Govt’s note to Soviets of November 17 transmitted my dispatch 151,
                    November 13 [<hi rend="italic">19</hi>].<note n="86" xml:id="d447fn86">Not
                        printed; but see footnote 41, <ref target="#pg_432">p. 432</ref>, and last
                        paragraph of telegram 971, November 21, 8 a.m., from Tehran, <ref
                            target="#pg_438">p. 438</ref>.</note> Final paragraph however seems so
                    important it is being sent in full in my following telegram<note n="87"
                        xml:id="d447fn87">No. 1040, <ref target="#pg_470">p. 470</ref>.</note> to
                    make sure Dept receives it accurately.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept as 1039, repeated Moscow as 306, London as 108.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
